{{orphan|date=April 2014}} {{DISPLAYTITLE:''SumAll''}} {{infobox company | name = SumAll | logo = [[File:SumAlllogo.jpg|right]] | location_city = [[New York City]] | location_country = USA | foundation = 2011 | key_people = [[Dane Atkinson]] <small>(CEO)</small> | industry = [[marketing analytics]] | homepage = [https://sumall.com/ www.sumall.com] }}
'''SumAll''' is a cross-platform marketing analytics company based in New York City. The company’s platform combines social media, web traffic, sales metrics and other data to allow customers to track business and social media metrics.
The company was launched 2011 by tech entrepreneur and former [[Squarespace]] CEO Dane Atkinson, with initial seed funding of $1.5 million from Battery Ventures, Wellington Partners, Matrix Partners and General Catalyst Partners.<ref>{{cite web|last=Heussner|first=Ki Mae|title=With $1.5M, SumAll brings data to the mom and pop shops of the Web|url=http://gigaom.com/2012/06/01/with-1-5m-sumall-brings-data-to-the-mom-and-pop-shops-of-the-web/|publisher=Gigaoam|accessdate=20 Mar 2014|date=1 Jun 2012}}</ref>
In 2014, SumAll was named one of the "10 Coolest New York Enterprise Startups Right Now" by ''Business Insider''.<ref>{{cite web|last=Graham|first=Mickey|title=These Are The 10 Coolest New York Enterprise Startups Right Now|url=http://www.businessinsider.com/10-coolest-nyc-enterprise-startups-2014-2/|publisher=Business Insider|accessdate=20 Mar 2014|date=6 Feb 2014}}</ref> SumAll's "open salary" policy,<ref>{{cite web|last=Zara|first=Christopher|title=The End Of Pay Secrecy? Jill Abramson Firing Underscores Debate Over Salary Transparency, And Some Diehard Capitalists Say It’s About Time|url=http://www.ibtimes.com/end-pay-secrecy-jill-abramson-firing-underscores-debate-over-salary-transparency-some-1585105|publisher=International Business Times|date=15 Mar 2014}}</ref> where compensation amounts for all employees are public, has also gained it considerable attention in the business press.
The company also supports a non-profit branch, SumAll.org,<ref>http://sumall.org/</ref> dedicated to supporting non-profits and charities through data analysis.
